  <title>ESP32-C3</title>
  <text xml:space="preserve"><note-content version="0.1">ESP32-C3

<datetime>Thursday, August 4, 2022, 10:27 PM</datetime>

Lolin/Wemos/NodeMCU C3-Mini boards have dtr/rts issue, In Arduino platform 

I compared boards.txt settings and found the trick.

Find these two lines:

esp32c3.serial.disableDTR=false
esp32c3.serial.disableRTS=false
Change them to:

esp32c3.serial.disableDTR=true
esp32c3.serial.disableRTS=true

After that, Serial Monitor works perfectly with "ESP32C3 Dev Module" selected.

<link:url>https://www.reddit.com/r/esp32/comments/pf61v1/esp32c3_serial_output_in_arduino_ide/</link:url>

<size:large>Own Python based Serial Monitor to debug</size:large>
I have created serial_monitor.py in CPP_Practice/python_utils repo</note-content></text>
